150
00:14:07,970 --> 00:14:09,096
FACULTY'S OFFICE

151
00:14:09,179 --> 00:14:11,515
Hey, Fujino.
Congratulations on your graduation.

152
00:14:12,683 --> 00:14:14,560
I'm sorry, but I need a favor.

153
00:14:14,643 --> 00:14:17,521
Could you give this graduation diploma
to Kyomoto for me?

154
00:14:17,605 --> 00:14:19,147
I'll give you her address.

155
00:14:19,231 --> 00:14:22,693
What? Why me?

156
00:14:23,944 --> 00:14:28,532
Well, even if you quit drawing
in sixth grade,

157
00:14:28,616 --> 00:14:31,326
you guys still worked together
on the newspaper manga.

158
00:14:31,409 --> 00:14:34,580
I'm sure Kyomoto would rather get it
from you than from an old man like me.

159
00:14:34,663 --> 00:14:37,374
Well, I'd rather not, really.

160
00:14:37,457 --> 00:14:38,917
Oh, come on.

161
00:14:39,417 --> 00:14:41,545
Do your teacher one last favor.

162
00:14:42,546 --> 00:14:44,381
- Seriously?
- Here.

163
00:14:47,092 --> 00:14:48,969
KYOMOTO

164
00:15:01,106 --> 00:15:02,482
No one's home?

165
00:15:06,028 --> 00:15:07,237
It's open.

166
00:15:14,327 --> 00:15:15,704
Hello?

167
00:15:16,789 --> 00:15:20,042
I'm here to deliver
your graduation diploma.

168
00:15:25,673 --> 00:15:27,758
I'll leave it here, okay?

169
00:15:30,928 --> 00:15:32,137
Someone's home.

170
00:15:38,310 --> 00:15:39,519
Excuse me.

171
00:15:40,270 --> 00:15:43,607
I brought your graduation diploma.

172
00:16:32,072 --> 00:16:34,449
KYOMOTO'S HOUSE

173
00:16:37,202 --> 00:16:39,579
Don't come out! Don't come out!

174
00:16:39,663 --> 00:16:42,082
Come out! Come out!

175
00:16:43,250 --> 00:16:45,252
<i>It's the world shut-in competition finals!</i>

176
00:16:45,335 --> 00:16:48,171
<i>Kyomoto is in first place
by a significant lead.</i>

177
00:16:49,506 --> 00:16:52,634
{\an8}KYOMOTO

178
00:17:00,558 --> 00:17:02,560
What am I even doing?

179
00:17:04,646 --> 00:17:05,480
Wait...

180
00:17:10,527 --> 00:17:11,486
No!

181
00:17:12,237 --> 00:17:13,196
Hey...

182
00:17:15,573 --> 00:17:18,243
I'm leaving your graduation diploma here!

183
00:17:19,077 --> 00:17:20,412
Goodbye!

184
00:17:35,302 --> 00:17:36,303
Fujino-sensei!

185
00:18:00,243 --> 00:18:01,369
Kyomoto?

186
00:18:15,508 --> 00:18:19,972
Every week, I got... I got the newspaper.

187
00:18:20,055 --> 00:18:24,434
I read your manga from the start,
since third grade.

188
00:18:26,019 --> 00:18:27,437
I... I...

189
00:18:27,520 --> 00:18:31,859
I'm a fan of yours, Fujino-sensei!

190
00:18:32,442 --> 00:18:33,861
Can I have your autograph?

191
00:18:37,072 --> 00:18:38,991
I don't have any paper!

192
00:18:40,242 --> 00:18:41,159
My back!

193
00:18:41,243 --> 00:18:43,536
Please sign the back of my jacket!

194
00:18:49,209 --> 00:18:50,168
Sure.

195
00:18:55,090 --> 00:18:59,677
My favorites are <i>Love Square</i> from the
second week of August in third grade,

196
00:18:59,761 --> 00:19:04,599
the <i>Sasaki</i> series you did
from January to March in fourth grade,

197
00:19:04,682 --> 00:19:09,396
and every single one
from fifth and sixth grades was brilliant.

198
00:19:09,479 --> 00:19:12,315
I couldn't always finish
my strips in time,

199
00:19:12,399 --> 00:19:15,235
but you did one every week
while attending school.

200
00:19:15,318 --> 00:19:18,113
I couldn't believe
you were a grade schooler like me.

201
00:19:18,571 --> 00:19:22,910
Your stories and drawings
kept getting better around fifth grade,

202
00:19:22,993 --> 00:19:24,661
I was sure of it.

203
00:19:25,954 --> 00:19:28,540
Fujino-sensei, you're a manga genius!

204
00:19:33,879 --> 00:19:35,797
So, why...

205
00:19:37,299 --> 00:19:41,887
Why did you stop drawing your strips
in the middle of sixth grade?

206
00:19:44,014 --> 00:19:45,390
Well, actually...

207
00:19:46,391 --> 00:19:49,394
I'm trying to come up with a story
for a manga competition.

208
00:19:49,477 --> 00:19:52,314
So basically,
I quit so that I could reach the next level.

209
00:19:54,066 --> 00:19:55,275
A manga competition?

210
00:19:57,819 --> 00:19:58,736
Amazing!

211
00:19:58,820 --> 00:20:02,032
I wanna see it! I totally wanna see it!
That's so amazing!

212
00:20:03,158 --> 00:20:04,784
I wanna see! I wanna see!

213
00:20:05,368 --> 00:20:08,413
Well, the idea's only in my head for now,

214
00:20:09,081 --> 00:20:11,208
but it's pretty much finished.

215
00:20:11,291 --> 00:20:14,252
Basically, all that's left
is to draw a draft and ink it.

216
00:20:16,213 --> 00:20:18,215
I wanna see! I wanna see!

217
00:20:21,093 --> 00:20:24,179
Then, I guess I could show you
when it's done.

218
00:20:32,645 --> 00:20:35,315
It's starting to rain. I should go.

219
00:20:36,733 --> 00:20:37,859
See you.

220
00:20:40,904 --> 00:20:41,989
See you.

221
00:22:01,276 --> 00:22:03,653
KNOCK FIRST

222
00:22:03,736 --> 00:22:06,614
METAL PARADE

223
00:22:20,962 --> 00:22:22,797
Wait for me.

224
00:22:25,800 --> 00:22:27,177
I'm home.

225
00:22:37,937 --> 00:22:39,022
Welcome back.

226
00:22:39,606 --> 00:22:42,609
You're still here?
Wait, you finished the background already?

227
00:22:43,193 --> 00:22:45,987
Yes. I don't go to school,
so it's a piece of cake.

228
00:22:46,779 --> 00:22:51,159
But it feels like we'll never
be able to finish all 45 pages.

229
00:22:51,243 --> 00:22:53,703
Yeah, and we've been drawing nonstop.

230
00:23:25,777 --> 00:23:28,155
METAL PARADE
BY KYO FUJINO

231
00:23:28,780 --> 00:23:30,740
{\an8}You two middle schoolers really drew this?

232
00:23:30,823 --> 00:23:32,950
Amazing. I'm impressed.

233
00:23:33,576 --> 00:23:36,913
But it took us an entire year
to finish it.

234
00:23:37,580 --> 00:23:39,874
And she's done all the backgrounds.

235
00:23:40,458 --> 00:23:44,837
No, no. Being able to finish a manga
as a middle school student is a feat.

236
00:23:48,175 --> 00:23:50,593
The drawings and story
are both high quality.

237
00:23:50,677 --> 00:23:53,263
{\an8}You could win an honorable mention
at the very least.

238
00:23:53,346 --> 00:23:55,557
{\an8}METAL PARADE
BY KYO FUJINO

239
00:24:13,908 --> 00:24:16,536
WEEKLY JUMP

240
00:24:25,753 --> 00:24:27,630
{\an8}RESULTS
13-YEAR-OLD DUO TAKES RUNNER-UP!

241
00:24:27,714 --> 00:24:30,091
1 MILLION YEN AWARD

242
00:24:30,175 --> 00:24:32,552
METAL PARADE
BY KYO FUJINO (13)

243
00:24:42,479 --> 00:24:43,313
Ta-da!

244
00:24:43,813 --> 00:24:45,732
I opened a bank account with my mom.

245
00:24:46,941 --> 00:24:48,109
Me too.

246
00:24:48,693 --> 00:24:50,695
And, guess what?

247
00:24:51,238 --> 00:24:52,071
Ta-da!

248
00:24:52,655 --> 00:24:54,282
I withdrew 100,000 yen.

249
00:25:04,334 --> 00:25:06,503
You could buy a house with that.

250
00:25:06,961 --> 00:25:08,546
Want to buy one?

251
00:25:10,089 --> 00:25:11,674
Let's go into town tomorrow.

252
00:25:12,259 --> 00:25:13,718
It's my treat.

253
00:25:14,302 --> 00:25:17,972
Don't you need to save that?

254
00:25:19,098 --> 00:25:22,644
Well, we're gonna draw more manga
and make loads of money anyway.

255
00:25:22,727 --> 00:25:26,105
So let's go eat tons of whipped cream
with this money.

256
00:25:29,651 --> 00:25:30,610
Yeah.

257
00:25:40,453 --> 00:25:42,372
CREPE FOREST

258
00:26:21,494 --> 00:26:23,871
Thank you for the treating me today.

259
00:26:24,539 --> 00:26:28,000
We spent like crazy,
but we only used 5,000 yen.

260
00:26:30,253 --> 00:26:33,047
I'm glad I came out of my room.

261
00:26:33,130 --> 00:26:33,965
What?

262
00:26:34,549 --> 00:26:39,011
To tell you the truth,
I was afraid to go out today.

263
00:26:39,971 --> 00:26:45,268
You see, I stopped going to school
because I was scared of people.

264
00:26:47,270 --> 00:26:51,774
But I had a really good time today.

265
00:26:53,192 --> 00:26:58,281
I started drawing because
I had nothing to do at home.

266
00:26:58,365 --> 00:27:01,409
But now I'm glad I did.

267
00:27:02,785 --> 00:27:06,581
Fujino, thank you
for getting me out of my room.

268
00:27:08,124 --> 00:27:10,167
You can thank me with 100,000 yen.

269
00:27:10,251 --> 00:27:11,085
What?

270
00:27:11,753 --> 00:27:12,712
Just kidding.

271
00:27:32,607 --> 00:27:34,233
THE SEA CITIES
BY KYO FUJINO

272
00:27:34,317 --> 00:27:35,485
MY HEART LIES WITH THE SEA

273
00:27:41,408 --> 00:27:44,369
THE CICADA HUMANS
BY KYO FUJINO

274
00:27:49,290 --> 00:27:50,833
THE MAN WHO ATE THE CRAB
BY KYO FUJINO

275
00:27:50,917 --> 00:27:52,293
BAGWORM
BY KYO FUJINO

276
00:28:19,446 --> 00:28:23,282
{\an8}THE WORLD OF BACKGROUND ART

277
00:28:35,378 --> 00:28:37,129
We're getting serialized?

278
00:28:37,213 --> 00:28:40,425
The editor-in-chief wants you to try it
after you graduate high school.

279
00:28:40,508 --> 00:28:43,094
You've already had seven one-shots
published at age 17!

280
00:28:43,678 --> 00:28:45,638
Honestly, it's happening a little late.

281
00:28:59,736 --> 00:29:02,113
I'm sorry, I...

282
00:29:03,740 --> 00:29:06,242
I want to go to art school.

283
00:29:07,034 --> 00:29:07,952
So...

284
00:29:09,036 --> 00:29:09,996
So,

285
00:29:10,622 --> 00:29:12,874
I can't help with the series.

286
00:29:16,794 --> 00:29:18,880
Where's this coming from all of a sudden?

287
00:29:20,131 --> 00:29:22,800
Well, I guess it's fine.

288
00:29:22,884 --> 00:29:25,302
You only draw the backgrounds anyway.

289
00:29:25,386 --> 00:29:28,347
I can just get assistants to handle that.

290
00:29:31,392 --> 00:29:34,896
But there's no point
in going to art school.

291
00:29:34,979 --> 00:29:37,857
I heard there are no job prospects
even with an art degree.

292
00:29:38,775 --> 00:29:39,609
Yeah.

293
00:29:40,151 --> 00:29:41,653
I know...

294
00:29:41,736 --> 00:29:44,697
And you'll have to talk
to lots of strangers, you know?

295
00:29:45,615 --> 00:29:48,493
I'll work on that.

296
00:29:50,828 --> 00:29:54,499
If you just stick with me,
everything will work out.

297
00:30:01,047 --> 00:30:04,676
I want to try living on my own,

298
00:30:05,342 --> 00:30:07,720
without having to rely on you.

299
00:30:10,431 --> 00:30:12,517
It'll be so boring! I guarantee you!

300
00:30:13,100 --> 00:30:14,018
No, it won't!

301
00:30:14,602 --> 00:30:16,103
It totally will be!

302
00:30:16,187 --> 00:30:19,857
Not to mention, there's no way
you can handle college life on your own!

303
00:30:20,775 --> 00:30:22,694
I can! I will learn how!

304
00:30:22,777 --> 00:30:23,986
You'll fail!

305
00:30:24,070 --> 00:30:27,406
You're too shy to even talk
to the cashier at the convenience store!

306
00:30:27,490 --> 00:30:29,241
I'll practice.

307
00:30:29,325 --> 00:30:30,284
You can't pull it off!

308
00:30:30,367 --> 00:30:32,078
- But...
- What?

309
00:30:40,503 --> 00:30:41,546
I want to...

310
00:30:42,463 --> 00:30:44,256
get better at drawing.

311
00:31:00,189 --> 00:31:02,024
WEEKLY JUMP

312
00:31:02,108 --> 00:31:04,026
SHARK KICK SERIES RANKING

313
00:31:04,110 --> 00:31:06,278
SHARK KICK VOLUME 1
BY KYO FUJINO

314
00:31:10,825 --> 00:31:12,451
SHARK KICK VOLUME 2
BY KYO FUJINO

315
00:31:16,956 --> 00:31:18,583
SHARK KICK VOLUME 3
BY KYO FUJINO

316
00:31:56,788 --> 00:31:59,666
SHARK KICK SERIES RANKING

317
00:31:59,749 --> 00:32:03,127
KYO FUJINO

318
00:32:03,210 --> 00:32:07,506
SHARK KICK RANKED NO. 1
ANIME ADAPTATION CONFIRMED!

319
00:32:15,014 --> 00:32:18,768
Yes. She works diligently,

320
00:32:19,686 --> 00:32:21,604
but it's just not working out.

321
00:32:21,688 --> 00:32:23,105
Is there anyone else?

322
00:32:27,610 --> 00:32:31,447
Right, yes. I need more assistants.

323
00:32:35,492 --> 00:32:38,287
She's fast, but...

324
00:32:42,041 --> 00:32:44,543
She doesn't give enough thought
to the full picture.

325
00:32:45,086 --> 00:32:48,589
I know it's hard to find someone good.

326
00:32:48,673 --> 00:32:52,301
<i>We have breaking news
from the Yamagata Broadcasting Station.</i>

327
00:32:53,135 --> 00:32:56,973
Right. I'll just have to do
what I can for now.

328
00:33:01,102 --> 00:33:03,437
No, sorry again for the trouble.

329
00:33:03,938 --> 00:33:05,982
Let's discuss it again some other time.

330
00:33:07,859 --> 00:33:09,610
Okay. Bye.

331
00:33:22,123 --> 00:33:23,207
<i>I repeat.</i>

332
00:33:23,708 --> 00:33:28,004
<i>Today at midday at an art university
in Yamagata City, Yamagata Prefecture,</i>

333
00:33:28,087 --> 00:33:29,714
<i>a man with no fixed address</i>

334
00:33:29,797 --> 00:33:33,926
<i>attacked students
using an axe-like weapon.</i>

335
00:33:34,468 --> 00:33:39,640
<i>The Yamagata police have arrested a man
believed to be the perpetrator.</i>

336
00:33:40,391 --> 00:33:43,895
<i>We are yet to receive
any information regarding the victims.</i>

337
00:33:44,478 --> 00:33:50,442
{\an8}<i>The police are investigating the case
as a possible indiscriminate attack.</i>

338
00:33:50,526 --> 00:33:52,028
CALLING
KYOMOTO

339
00:34:09,336 --> 00:34:11,213
MOM
INCOMING CALL

340
00:34:27,688 --> 00:34:30,817
If our manga ever gets serialized,

341
00:34:30,900 --> 00:34:32,819
I want the artwork
to be super high quality.

342
00:34:33,402 --> 00:34:35,947
But I draw really slow.

343
00:34:36,781 --> 00:34:39,283
I wish I could draw faster.

344
00:34:39,867 --> 00:34:41,327
That's easy.

345
00:34:41,869 --> 00:34:44,413
If your drawing skills improve,
so will your speed.

346
00:34:44,496 --> 00:34:46,749
I plan on improving mine.

347
00:34:47,333 --> 00:34:50,377
Then, I'll work on my drawing skills too.

348
00:34:51,003 --> 00:34:52,463
Like you, Fujino.

349
00:34:53,089 --> 00:34:57,301
Awesome. Keep your eyes on my back and you'll grow too.

350
00:35:10,439 --> 00:35:12,817
{\an8}BREAKING NEWS
ART SCHOOL MASSACRE KILLER ARRESTED

351
00:35:12,900 --> 00:35:14,777
12 DEAD
3 GRAVELY INJURED

352
00:35:14,861 --> 00:35:17,238
{\an8}STRUCK THE BODIES MULTIPLE TIMES

353
00:35:17,321 --> 00:35:20,199
"THE ART I POSTED ON THE INTERNET
WAS PLAGIARIZED"

354
00:35:20,282 --> 00:35:24,161
{\an8}SHARK KICK HIATUS ANNOUNCEMENT
THANK YOU FOR ALL YOUR SUPPORT

355
00:36:11,458 --> 00:36:13,836
WEEKLY JUMP
SHARK KICK

356
00:37:19,443 --> 00:37:20,277
DON'T COME OUT!

357
00:37:20,361 --> 00:37:21,195
COME OUT! COME OUT!

358
00:37:21,278 --> 00:37:22,488
SHUT-IN COMPETITION FINALS!

359
00:37:22,571 --> 00:37:24,531
KYOMOTO IS IN FIRST PLACE
BY A SIGNIFICANT LEAD

360
00:37:24,615 --> 00:37:25,449
KYOMOTO

361
00:37:25,532 --> 00:37:28,410
DON'T COME OUT!

362
00:37:30,997 --> 00:37:33,624
COME OUT! COME OUT!

363
00:37:42,383 --> 00:37:43,634
It's my fault.

364
00:37:45,928 --> 00:37:47,596
<i>It's because...</i>

365
00:37:49,598 --> 00:37:51,225
<i>I drew this manga that day.</i>

366
00:38:00,692 --> 00:38:03,112
Kyomoto died...

367
00:38:04,238 --> 00:38:05,697
because of me.

368
00:38:07,533 --> 00:38:12,204
<i>If I hadn't gotten her out of her room,
she wouldn't have died.</i>

369
00:38:21,922 --> 00:38:22,756
<i>Why?</i>

370
00:38:25,217 --> 00:38:26,218
<i>Why?</i>

371
00:38:27,803 --> 00:38:30,014
Why did I draw this?

372
00:38:34,601 --> 00:38:37,396
Drawing is completely useless...

373
00:39:07,759 --> 00:39:09,470
"Don't come out"?

374
00:39:19,271 --> 00:39:20,606
Hello?

375
00:39:20,689 --> 00:39:23,484
I'm here to deliver
your graduation diploma.

376
00:39:24,651 --> 00:39:27,363
I'll leave it here, okay?

377
00:39:51,678 --> 00:39:53,430
Must be a ghost.

378
00:40:19,623 --> 00:40:21,500
LETTER OF ACCEPTANCE

379
00:40:41,437 --> 00:40:46,358
{\an8}SECOND FLOOR OF THE ART DEPARTMENT
WESTERN ART COURSE BUILDING

380
00:40:52,823 --> 00:40:57,453
{\an8}A STUDENT SITS ON A SOFA FOR A BREAK

381
00:40:57,536 --> 00:41:01,915
{\an8}SHE HEARS A METALLIC KNOCKING SOUND
FROM THE STAIRCASE

382
00:41:05,502 --> 00:41:09,381
{\an8}THERE ARE NO OTHER STUDENTS
NEAR THE SOFA

383
00:41:11,925 --> 00:41:15,804
{\an8}AT 11:19 A.M., A MAN ENTERS FROM
THE OUTDOOR STAIRS AND SEES THE STUDENT

384
00:41:26,190 --> 00:41:30,068
{\an8}HE IS HOLDING A POINTED TOOL
HE FOUND AT THE ART PRACTICE BUILDING

385
00:41:32,279 --> 00:41:33,280
Hey, you.

386
00:41:33,905 --> 00:41:34,906
I mean...

387
00:41:36,408 --> 00:41:37,909
You. I'm talking to you.

388
00:41:40,871 --> 00:41:42,122
At the exhibition,

389
00:41:42,206 --> 00:41:45,041
there was an artwork
that looked like mine, right?

390
00:41:47,753 --> 00:41:49,463
- My...
- Sorry?

391
00:41:52,466 --> 00:41:55,761
{\an8}The artwork I posted online!
There was an exact copy, right?

392
00:41:55,844 --> 00:41:58,180
{\an8}THE MAN SAID HE INTENDED TO KILL
ANY ART STUDENT HE SAW

393
00:42:16,657 --> 00:42:19,451
Don't you dare look down on me!

394
00:42:20,911 --> 00:42:22,704
That was my idea!

395
00:42:23,997 --> 00:42:26,082
You stole my art!

396
00:42:48,897 --> 00:42:51,942
I practice karate at the dojo
in the neighboring town.

397
00:42:52,025 --> 00:42:53,402
I was jogging

398
00:42:53,485 --> 00:42:56,029
when I saw this guy
going into campus with a weapon.

399
00:42:56,112 --> 00:42:57,781
I knew he was trouble,

400
00:42:57,864 --> 00:43:01,785
so I ran after him and when I gave him
a karate kick, I fell and broke my leg.

401
00:43:01,868 --> 00:43:03,245
Pretty lame, isn't it?

402
00:43:08,417 --> 00:43:10,419
Thank you very much.

403
00:43:11,253 --> 00:43:14,256
I'd like to thank you properly,

404
00:43:14,923 --> 00:43:18,635
so can I have your phone number?

405
00:43:19,219 --> 00:43:20,762
Yeah, sure thing.

406
00:43:24,308 --> 00:43:25,476
{\an8}Fujino.

407
00:43:26,602 --> 00:43:27,978
{\an8}Fujino-sensei.

408
00:43:28,645 --> 00:43:31,523
Are you Fujino-sensei by any chance?

409
00:43:32,148 --> 00:43:33,317
Sensei?

410
00:43:33,400 --> 00:43:34,943
When you were in grade school,

411
00:43:35,026 --> 00:43:38,280
did you draw four-panel manga strips
for the school newspaper?

412
00:43:38,864 --> 00:43:41,742
Yeah, I did, now that you mention it.

413
00:43:41,825 --> 00:43:43,285
It really is you!

414
00:43:43,369 --> 00:43:45,954
I was a fan of your four-panel manga.

415
00:43:47,289 --> 00:43:49,416
What a coincidence, right?

416
00:43:49,500 --> 00:43:50,751
Thanks.

417
00:43:50,834 --> 00:43:52,419
Sorry, but it's time to go.

418
00:44:00,218 --> 00:44:03,972
Why did you quit drawing manga?

419
00:44:09,895 --> 00:44:12,398
I recently started drawing again.

420
00:44:12,481 --> 00:44:15,025
If my manga gets serialized,
be my assistant, okay?

421
00:44:52,228 --> 00:44:53,439
I'm home.

422
00:45:12,708 --> 00:45:13,667
FIRST KISS BY FUJINO

423
00:45:13,750 --> 00:45:15,586
- KISS ME AGAIN WHEN WE'RE REINCARNATED.
- I WILL.

424
00:46:18,815 --> 00:46:21,735
<i>- I'll kill you!
- Ahhh!</i>

425
00:46:21,818 --> 00:46:23,194
<i>- Take this!
- Agh!</i>

426
00:46:24,154 --> 00:46:25,864
<i>You're Fujino-sensei!</i>

427
00:46:25,947 --> 00:46:27,491
<i>You are not hurt?</i>

428
00:46:28,158 --> 00:46:29,910
<i>Then my work here is done.</i>

429
00:46:31,537 --> 00:46:34,915
LOOK BACK BY KYOMOTO

430
00:47:25,256 --> 00:47:28,176
SHARK KICK BY KYO FUJINO

431
00:47:30,971 --> 00:47:33,599
READER QUESTIONNAIRE

432
00:47:49,447 --> 00:47:53,451
AYUMU FUJINO

433
00:48:00,333 --> 00:48:02,628
<i>You know, for starters,</i>

434
00:48:03,253 --> 00:48:05,756
<i>I don't even like drawing manga.</i>

435
00:48:06,297 --> 00:48:10,677
<i>It's not fun, just plain tedious
and super unglamorous too.</i>

436
00:48:11,386 --> 00:48:14,973
<i>I can draw all day long
and still be nowhere near finished.</i>

437
00:48:16,057 --> 00:48:17,976
<i>I should stick to reading them.</i>

438
00:48:18,769 --> 00:48:20,061
<i>Drawing isn't for me.</i>

439
00:48:26,735 --> 00:48:30,155
<i>Then why do you draw, Fujino?</i>

440
00:48:59,350 --> 00:49:01,645
METAL PARADE (WORKING TITLE)
BY AYUMU FUJINO

441
00:50:03,749 --> 00:50:06,668
{\an8}SEPTEMBER
DEADLINE

442
00:50:32,193 --> 00:50:35,739
{\an8}METAL PARADE

443
00:51:10,690 --> 00:51:16,696
{\an8}IT'S SHARK TIME, BABY!
TO BE CONTINUED IN VOLUME 12!

